             (Police-constable G 118). I saw the prisoner in Radnor-street, City-road, on the 15th of October; I saw Edwards running, and carrying this basket, which was covered with this apron - Rogers was behind him, but had nothing; it was between five and six hundred yards from the prosecutor's - I took Edwards, and Lapthorn took Rogers; I found the owner of the property.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18321018-224-person1949">
                  JOHN 
                  LAPTHORN
               <interp inst="t18321018-224-person1949" type="surname" value="LAPTHORN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18321018-224-person1949" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18321018-224-person1949" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             (Police-constable C 102). I saw the prisoners running together; I heard Edwards say to Rogers "Come along" - we run after them; Rogers run off, I followed and took him.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18321018-224-person1950">
                  MARGARET 
                  BROWN
               <interp inst="t18321018-224-person1950" type="surname" value="BROWN"></interp>
